# Studio camera udev rules — Phase 1 of camera 24/7 resilience epic.
# See docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-12-camera-247-resilience-epic.md § Phase 1.
#
# Disable USB autosuspend for studio cameras (BRIO 046d:085e and C920 046d:08e5).
# USB autosuspend is a documented contributor to webcam disappearance in
# 24/7 deployments. These cameras are not power-budget-constrained; there is
# no benefit to letting the kernel power them down.
#
# Phase 3 (recovery state machine + pyudev integration) extends this file with
# TAG+="systemd" + ENV{SYSTEMD_USER_WANTS} entries to trigger v4l2-ctl
# reconfiguration on USB re-enumeration. That work does not land until Phase 3
# and the relevant rules are commented out here until then.

# BRIO 4K (046d:085e)
ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="046d", ATTR{idProduct}=="085e", ATTR{power/control}="on"

# C920 (046d:08e5)
ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="046d", ATTR{idProduct}=="08e5", ATTR{power/control}="on"
